main event: A possible satellite or meteor was observed in the Pacific Ocean for 15 seconds.
interesting points: The object appeared as a 'shooting star' and was observed at coordinates 43.2N 172.5W in the Pacific Ocean.
The object was observed at an elevation of 50 degrees and traveled from 135 to 360 degrees true for 15 seconds.
The report indicates the observation may have been of a satellite crossing the equator at 141.6W at 0832Z.
The general description and duration of the observation is more consistent with a meteor sighting.
The report was submitted as a CIRVIS (Communications Instructions for Reporting Vital Intelligence Sightings) report.
